Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deletePinGroup(25.10)                                    deletePinGroup(25.10)

Name
       deletePinGroup  -  Deletes a pin group or all pin groups that were cre-
       ated earlier

Syntax
       deletePinGroup

       [-help]

       [-cell <cellName>]

       -pinGroup <pinGroupName>

       Deletes a pin group or all pin groups that were created earlier.

Parameters
       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the name of the module. The module  name  is  not  re-
              quired if the command is run on a top-level module.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each deletePinGroup parameter.  For  a  detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:

              man deletePinGroup

       -pinGroup <pinGroupName>
              Specifies the name of the pin group that was created.  Wildcards
              accepted.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
              * The following command deletes the pin group PinGroup17 of mod-
                ule SH17:

                deletePinGroup -cell SH17 -pinGroup PinGroup17

              * The follow command deletes all the pin groups of module SH17:

                deletePinGroup -cell SH17 -pinGroup *

Related Information
              * createPinGroup

              * addPinToPinGroup

              * deletePinFromPinGroup

